la do the above calculations in  suggest?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
110 "sum = 2^n.  For example the 13th. row would be 2^13. Row 1 is 2^1
 =2; row 2 is 2^2 =4 ; row 3 is 2^3 = 8; etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 388 "2.  Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal'
s Triangle.   Use Maple to construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Tri
angle. (The trick will be to get the coefficients to occur in the corr
ect order.  The Maple command for generating a sequence might be helpf
ul. It is   seq(expression(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an exp
ression with index i and m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 3 "   " }}{EXCHG {PARA 12 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 57 "for r from 0 to 10 do seq(coeff((a+
1)^r,a,i), i=0..r) od;" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 
