{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 2 "  " }{TEXT 279 58 "What's \+
the famous formula we get when we solve p3=0 for x?" }}{EXCHG {PARA 
258 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "The Quadratic Formula." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 169 "  See if MAPLE knows a g
eneral formula for solving general cubic polynomials, i.e. is there a \+
3rd order formula comparable to the quadratic formula?  If so, exhibit
 it. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "p3:=a*x^2+b*x+c;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>
%#p3G,(*&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"#F(F(*&%\"bGF(F*F(F(%\"cGF(" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "p4:=a*x^3+b*x^2+c*x+d;" }}{PARA 11 
"" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p4G,**&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"$F(F(*&%\"bGF()F
*\"\"#F(F(*&%\"cGF(F*F(F(%\"dGF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p4=0,x);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6%,(*
(\"\"'!\"\"%\"aGF&,***\"#O\"\"\"%\"cGF+%\"bGF+F'F+F+*(\"$3\"F+%\"dGF+)
F'\"\"#F+F&*&\"\")F+)F-\"\"$F+F&**\"#7F+F6#F+F2,,*(\"\"%F+)F,F6F+F'F+F
+*&)F,F2F+)F-F2F+F&*,\"#=F+F,F+F-F+F'F+F0F+F&*(\"#FF+)F0F2F+F1F+F+*(F<
F+F0F+F5F+F+F9F'F+F+#F+F6F+*,F2F+F6F&,&*(F6F+F,F+F'F+F+*$F@F+F&F+F'F&F
(#F&F6F&*(F6F&F-F+F'F&F&,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F-
F+F'F&F&*(^#F9F+F6F9,&*(F%F&F'F&F(FGF+*,F2F+F6F&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+F+F+,**(
F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F-F+F'F&F&*(^##F&F2F+F6F9FTF+F
+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 280 111 "Why do you t
hink high school students are never asked to remember the general form
ula for the roots of a cubic?" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 65 "I
t is extremely long and students would consider it unreasonable." }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "4.  Solv
ing Equations in One Variable.   There are two different commands to d
irect Maple to solve an equation:  " }{TEXT 285 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 5 
" and " }{TEXT 286 7 "fsolve." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "They hav
e different purposes.  The " }{TEXT 287 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 63 " comma
nd attempts to find exact solutions.  If the expression  " }{TEXT 289 
1 "f" }{TEXT -1 116 "  is defined in terms of only one variable, there
 are several different ways to direct Maple to solve the equation  " }
{TEXT 290 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 291 4 "0.  " }{TEXT -1 54 "The following al
l cause Maple to solve the equation   " }{TEXT 292 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 
293 2 "0." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
16 "       solve(f);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f,x)
;" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f=0);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 20 "       solve(f=0,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 349 "Maple makes an assumption that if the c
oefficients of a polynomial are all given exactly (as integers or rati
onal numbers [ratios of integer]), then you are only interested in fin
ding exact solutions.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra doesn't guar
antee that the solutions of  a polynomial can be found exactly, only t
he polynomial has solutions.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 78 "You can force Maple to report additional \+
(approximate) solutions by using the " }{TEXT 288 6 "fsolve" }{TEXT 
-1 42 " command.  (What does the \"f\" stand for?) " }{TEXT 297 29 "It
 stands for floating point." }{TEXT -1 3 " In" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 249 "addition, to forcing Maple to report approximate solutio
ns, you can specify a field extension (typically real or complex) and \+
require Maple to look for solutions which fit in that field extension.
  Also, one can specify a range of x values and force" }{TEXT 296 7 " \+
fsolve" }{TEXT -1 75 " to only look for solutions in that specified ra
nge.  For example, compare:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "fsolve(4*x-x^3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "
" {XPPMATH 20 "6%$!+++++?!\"*$\"\"!F'$\"+++++?F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 57 "This sets the equation = to 0 and solves for the 3
 roots." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "fsolve(4*x-x^3,x
=1..4);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+++++?!\"*" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 90 "This sets the equation = to 0 and gives o
nly one root because x can only be 1, 2, 3, or 4." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 28 "For each of the polynomials " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p[1]" "6#&%
\"pG6#\"\"\"" }{TEXT -1 9 " through " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p[14]" "6#&%\"pG
6#\"#9" }{TEXT -1 19 ", do the following:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
56 "     a.   solve for all exact roots whereever possible, " }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 59 "     b.   find all approximate roots to 10 deci
mal places, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 43 "     c.  factor each into
 linear factors.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 106 "You will need to click on  [> in the toolbar to obtain n
ew execution lines just below the cursor position." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "p1 := x^2-2;
    " }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p1G,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F*F
)!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "solve(p1);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$*$\"\"##\"\"\"F$,$F#!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "fsolve(p1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6$$!+iN@99!\"*$\"+iN@99F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "factor(p1,real);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*
&,&%\"xG\"\"\"$\"+iN@99!\"*F&F&,&F%F&$\"+iN@99F)!\"\"F&" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 58 "This p1 is defined to distinguish it from
