"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "5.  Solving Systems of Equations in Several Var
iables.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
49 "When we have an equation in two variables, e.g.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 
"3*x -2*y = 5" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&
" }{TEXT -1 147 "  we often associate with it a graph, the set of poin
ts (x,y) in the two-dimensional plane which satisfy the equation.  For
 a linear equation like " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x-2*y = 5" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"
\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 89 " the graph is a
 straight line.  For more a complicated equation in two variables, e.g
.,  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "2*x^3 -3*x + y^2 = x*y" "6#/,(*&\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"
xG\"\"$F'F'*&F*F'F)F'!\"\"*$%\"yGF&F'*&F)F'F.F'" }{TEXT -1 45 "  the g
raph becomes a more complicated curve." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 282 "When we have two equations in two va
riables, we think of the solution set of this system of equations as b
eing the set of points (x,y) which satisfy both equations simultaneous
ly.  In terms of their graphs, the solution set is the set of points w
here the graphs intersect (cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 622 "When we have two linear equations in t
wo variables, since their graphs are straight lines, then two straight
 lines, if they cross, will cross in exactly one place.  Hence, the so
lution set of the system of equations will be exactly one point (x,y).
  If we have two equations which are more complicated, then the number
 of intersection points (crossing points) of their graphs can vary.  F
or example, if the graph of one equation is a circle and the graph of \+
the other equation is a straight line, then, if their graphs cross, th
en number of solutions (intersection points) of the system of equation
s could be 1 or 2.  Etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 128 "We can instruct Maple to find solutions of system
s of equations using the solve or fsolve commands.  The syntax for doi
ng so is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
30 "     solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 "
 " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 85 "where eq1 and eq2 are equations in t
he variables x and y.  This is illustrated below." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "solve(\{ x +
 2*y = 5, 2*x-3*y = -1\},\{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#
<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "We could have defined " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 40 "eq1 := x + 2*y = 5;\neq2 := 2*x-3*y = -1;" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&%\"xG\"\"\"*&\"\"#F(%\"yGF(F
(\"\"&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq2G/,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xG
F)F)*&\"\"$F)%\"yGF)!\"\"F." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 26 "and then given the command" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 55 "and achieved the same res
ult.  Remember the solution  (" }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "13/7" "6#*&\"#8\"\"\"
\"\"(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "11/7" "6#*&\"#6\"\"\"\"\"
(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 127 ") represents a point in the two-dimensional pla
ne (why two-dimensional?) where the graphs of the equations intersect \+
(cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 63 "Find the solutions, if they exist, for the following equations \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "a.  " 
}{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x - 2*y = 6" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%
\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"'" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "4*x + y = -2" "6#/
,&*&\"\"%\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'%\"yGF',$\"\"#!\"\"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 4 "b.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "6*x -9*y = 12" "6#/,&*&\"\"'\"\"\"%\"xGF'F
'*&\"\"*F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"#7" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*y - 2*
x = 3" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"yGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"xGF'!\"\"F&" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "c.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "y = x - x^2" "6#/%\"yG,&%\"x
G\"\"\"*$F&\"\"#!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "y = x-4" "6#/
%\"yG,&%\"xG\"\"\"\"\"%!\"\"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "d.  " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "x^2 + y^2 = 16" "6#/,&*$%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"yGF'F(\"#;
" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "x^2/36 + y^2/4 = 1" "6#/,&*&%\"xG
\"\"#\"#O!\"\"\"\"\"*&%\"yGF'\"\"%F)F*F*" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "e.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "x^2+y^2 = 16
" "6#/,&*$%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"yGF'F(\"#;" }{TEXT -1 4 ",   " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "x + y = 6" "6#/,&%\"xG\"\"\"%\"yGF&\"\"'" }{TEXT -1 4 "
    " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 34 "solve(\{3*x-2*y=6,4*
x+y=-2\},\{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"xG#\"\"#\"
#6/%\"yG#!#IF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 "Remember the pr
ogram is case sensitive." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 38 
"solve(\{6*x-9*y=12, 3*y-2*x=3\}, \{x,y\});" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 32 "These 2 equation are apparently " }{TEXT 299 8 "paralle
l" }{TEXT -1 15 " and therefore " }{TEXT 298 22 "do not have a solutio
n" }{TEXT -1 135 " (they do not intersect.).  If  one of the numbers i
s changed, it will give a point of intersection and will therefore hav
e a solution." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 11 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 31 "solve(\{y=x-x^2, y=x-4\}, \{x,y\});
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$<$/%\"xG\"\"#/%\"yG!\"#<$/F%F)/F(!
\"'" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 36 "solve(\{x^2+y^2=16, \+
x^2/36+y^2/4=1\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG-%'RootO
fG6#,&\"\"&!\"\"*&\"\"#\"\"\")%#_ZGF-F.F./%\"xG,$*&\"\"$F.-F'6$,&*&F-F
.F/F.F.F5F+/%&labelG%$_L3GF.F." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 9 "evalf(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG$\"+I)Q6e
